"{'title': 'Adversarial Multi-task Learning for Text Classification', 'authors': [{'forename': 'Pengfei', 'surname': 'Liu', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'School of Computer Science', 'affiliation_country': 'China'}, {'forename': 'Xipeng', 'surname': 'Qiu', 'email': 'xpqiu@fudan.edu.cn', 'affiliation_name': 'School of Computer Science', 'affiliation_country': 'China'}, {'forename': 'Xuanjing', 'surname': 'Huang', 'email': 'xjhuang@fudan.edu.cn', 'affiliation_name': 'School of Computer Science', 'affiliation_country': 'China'}], 'abstract': 'Neural network models have shown their promising opportunities for multi-task learning, which focus on learning the shared layers to extract the common and task-invariant features. However, in most existing approaches, the extracted shared features are prone to be contaminated by task-specific features or the noise brought by other tasks. In this paper, we propose an adversarial multi-task learning framework, alleviating the shared and private latent feature spaces from interfering with each other. We conduct extensive experiments on 16 different text classification tasks, which demonstrates the benefits of our approach. Besides, we show that the shared knowledge learned by our proposed model can be regarded as off-the-shelf knowledge and easily transferred to new tasks. The datasets of all 16 tasks are publicly available at http://nlp.fudan. edu.cn/data/', 'acknowledgements': '<ontology_classes.Aknowledgement object at 0x000002937430F8D0>', 'references': [{'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x0000029374399490>, 'date': None}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x0000029374399410>, 'date': '2014'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x0000029374399510>, 'date': '2010'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x0000029374399590>, 'date': '2007'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x0000029374399B10>, 'date': '2007'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x00000293743994D0>, 'dat